Developing a REST-API to query immunedb through implementation of the ADC API 

immunedb (immunedb.com) is a pipeline developed to store and analyse high-throughput B and T cell sequencing data. 
In order to expand the abilities of iReceptor to iReceptorPlus and also to make immunedb data and tools accessible and reachable to more scientists and research groups, we developed a new REST-API for immunedb which enables immunedb to be a repository that responses to queries and especially ADC API queries.Therefore we implemented the AIRR Data Commons (ADC) API, which provides two primary endpoints for querying and retrieving AIRR-seq data: the Repertoire (the metadata) and the Rearrangement endpoints.

The new immunedb API will not only allow programmatic access to query and download AIRR-seq data but will also provide an additional clone relationship endpoint that can help build further developments of the ADC API.
